OL,3,CFourteen train passengers treated
OL,4,Cafter 'smell of chemicals' reported
OL,6,FLondon Fire Brigade (LFB) said in a
OL,7,Fstatement: "Firefighters were called
OL,8,Fto a report of a smell of chemicals on
OL,9,Fan Elizabeth line platform at
OL,10,FFarringdon station this morning.
OL,12,F"Crews attended and carried out a
OL,13,Fsweep of the area to check for
OL,14,Felevated readings of any chemical
OL,15,Fsubstances. No elevated readings were
OL,16,Fdetected.
OL,18,F"Fourteen people were treated at the
OL,19,Fscene with two of those people taken
OL,20,Fto hospital by London Ambulance
OL,21,FService as a precaution."
OL,26,@oD@LOUtD@AOUzD@AOU}D@YO]
